  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Shared Interest Organisational Development Phase 1</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SIF is the charitable arm of fair trade lender SISL. SIF&#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x2122;s capacity building projects enable producers to build sustainable businesses that provide secure livelihoods. It began with small projects and attracted grants of &#xC2;&#xA3;235,000 for a project in Rwanda and &#xC2;&#xA3;502,000 for a project in Swaziland. Positioned for growth, SIF has a unique opportunity to build on the track-record of major grant management and project impact built up over the past 3 years. To consolidate this position and move forward, the organisation recognises the need to review its current situation, build on the lessons learned, and move the organisation on to its next stage of development. SIF plans to undertake an organisational assessment, focusing on leadership, strategy, structure and governance, including SIF&#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x2122;s relationship with SISL. The aim is to provide information, from which SIF can increase the benefit derived from the relationship with SISL; ensure appropriate, efficient and effective governance; align structure with strategy; and as a result streamline processes and communications. By developing this clarity, alignment and improved internal processes SIF aims to increase its ability to run projects efficiently, fundraise effectively and communicate clearly; benefiting producers with increased capability in planning, research opportunities, fundraising, and implementing new projects.</narrative>
  </description>
